      • calcCandidateScore

        public double calcCandidateScore(CandidateFluxDomain cfd)

        Parameters:
        cfd - the candidate flux domain
        Returns:
        the candidate score

                                                           long endTime,
                                                           java.lang.String domainfile)
                                                             throws java.lang.Exception
        Load candidate flux domains from the data files for the time period between the start and end times.
        Parameters:
        startTime - the start time
        endTime - the end time
        domainfile - a file containing the list of domains that should be clustered regardless of the candidate score. If null the list is ignored.
        Returns:
        the list of candidate flux domains
        Throws:

                                             long endTime,
                                             boolean selcfds)
                                               throws java.lang.Exception
        Runs the clustering process on the data files for the time period between the start and end times. The linkage type and max cut height are read from the ClusterGenerator.properties file
        Parameters:
        startTime - the start time
        endTime - the end time
        selcfds - if true then the file with a list of domains to cluster regardless of candidate score is used for clustering
        Returns:
        the list of clusters
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if there is an error reading the ClusterGenerator.properties or data files
